        "taskDescription": {
            "construction": [
                "A battery, zener diode and resistor are connected in series as shown.  Note that the battery's negative terminal is attached to the anode of the diode.  Construct a model of the circuit assuming that the battery is 12 volts, the resistor is 400 ohms and the breakdown voltage of the zener diode is 10 volts."
            ],
            "incremental": [
                "A battery, zener diode and resistor are connected in series as shown.  Note that the battery's negative terminal is attached to the anode of the diode."
            ],
            "execution": [
                "This is a model of the circuit shown above that has a resistor in series with a zener diode.  Note that if a current flows, it flows clockwise.  If this were an ordinary diode, it would be reverse biased and no current would flow.  However, in this circuit, the zener diode has a breakdown voltage of 10 and the battery voltage is greater, 12 volts, so just enough current flows through the zener diode so that it drops 10 volts and the resistor drops the remaining 2 volts."
            ]
        },
